article_title: Fed’s Kashkari Sees Moderate Growth for U.S. Economy
article_text:
NEW YORK—In some of his first direct comments on the economic outlook, newly installed Minneapolis Fed President Neel Kashkari said Tuesday that he sees the U.S. economy continuing to grow as the year progresses.

“I feel pretty good about how the U.S. is positioned” for growth, Mr. Kashkari said while speaking at an event in Bloomington, Minn. “The moderate economic outlook is still the base case” for what is likely to happen over...
